(10, 1, '2013-01-18 17:02:53', '2013-01-18 17:02:53', '<h2>Me. Elsewhere.</h2>\r\nProgramming makes up a huge chunk of my life. I (sometimes) write about what I''m currently up to at <a href="http://kodeplay.skytreader.net">{kode.play();}</a>. My (side) programming projects which I''ve deemed "done" (though not necessarily "finished"), are at my <a href="http://kode.skytreader.net">portfolio website</a>. Those which I''m still actively working on can be seen at my <a href="http://https://github.com/skytreader" target="_blank">GitHub</a> account.\r\n\r\nI''m also interested in photography. I haven''t bothered compiling a proper photography portfolio (contrast to my programming projects) but if anyone asks for one on the fly I''d give them my <a href="http://chadestioco.deviantart.com/" target="_blank">DeviantArt account</a>. I''m also at <a href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/lokisky_walker/" target="_blank">Flickr</a>; that''s where you''d find almost all the photographs in this blog as well as some which did not make it to DeviantArt but still got a story or two to tell.\r\n<h2>You should totally visit...</h2>\r\nThe geek webcomic, <a href="http://xkcd.com/" target="_blank">xkcd</a>. Great wonder at what a person can do with just stick figures. A total must read for people in Computer Science/Math/Physics/Fine Arts. Well, any field, really.\r\n\r\nAnd this guy definitely deserves more attention: the French artist <a href="http://english.bouletcorp.com/" target="_blank">Boulet</a> (English-website linked). I discovered him in 2012 and he inspired me to do sketches again, a skill I quite acquired during my elementary days, used every now and then during high school, and then very sparingly during my undergrad.\r\n\r\nI should also mention <a href="http://thoughtcatalog.com/" target="_blank">Thought Catalog</a>. One day, I got depressed. According to (cheap) movies with themes like that, my next logical move should be to down twenty rounds of beer. But that day, I read twenty TC articles instead. Never had beer but I guess the effect is equivalent.\r\n\r\nLast but not the least,<a href="http://www.aeonmagazine.com/" target="_blank"> Aeon Magazine</a>. It''s my Thought Catalog when I''m not feeling depressed but feeling high and intellectual, as if the singularity that will silence all human hubris is just around the corner, waiting to humble the next pair of eyes that gazes upon it.', 'Links', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'links', '', '', '2013-02-09 10:05:50', '2013-02-09 10:05:50', '', 0, 'http://localhost/skytreader.net/?page_id=10', 0, 'page', '', 0),
