(13, 1, '2012-12-22 07:24:15', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '<h1>chad n. /tʃæd/</h1>\r\n<h2>chocolate-consuming, code-churning creature</h2>\r\nI code. I shoot. I blog about what I code and what I shoot.\r\n<h2>I''m a reader</h2>\r\nYep. Perhaps one of my earliest passions. Like most people my age, I''m a huge fan of J.K. Rowling''s Harry Potter. I''m also a huge fan of Neil Gaiman (and his epic, <i>The Sandman</i>). From Rowling and Gaiman, I picked up a whole slew of other authors to read like Lovecraft, Funke, and Lewis.\r\n\r\nThe literature course I took in college introduced me to a whole bunch of other authors. I did not appreciate everything in our reading list for that class but, among those I did, I ended up being fond of Italo Calvino and Arturo Perez-Reverte. Reading discussions about their work made me curious about other authors such as Umberto Eco and Aldous Huxley. Perez-Reverte made me check out other thrillers like Elizabeth Kostova''s <em>The Historian</em> and Graham Moore''s <em>The Sherlockian</em> ((If you managed to deduce that I''ve also read all the canonical Holmes stories, congrats!)).\r\n<h2>I''m a writer</h2>\r\n<h2>I''m a photodocumanitarian</h2>\r\n<h2>I''m a maker</h2>', 'Stuff I Do', '', 'draft', 'open', 'open', '', 'stuff-i-do', '', '', '2013-01-11 22:59:13', '2013-01-11 22:59:13', '', 0, 'http://localhost/skytreader.net/?page_id=13', 0, 'page', '', 0),
